<br>
US dominance of nuclear weapons won't help them in this regard and if someone decides to use nukes against the US it will probably be after there is no hope of them winning through more conventional methods.  In that case being able to destroy the country won't do any good because by the time they set them off they won't have a country to destroy.<br>
<br>
Terrorists are harder to deal with.  The biggest problem with them is that they are very hard to find and often manage to hide out inside a city far too close to civilians for nuclear weapons to be of any use getting rid of them.  Even when they're well away from the cities using them could be problematic for diplomatic reasons as well as the fact that it might cause another country to launch their nukes (if Russia think the nuke is heading for them they'll launch, then the US will launch back).<br>
<br>
There aren't many targets that can't be hit with a conventional weapon.  Bunker busting bombs are very good at destroying targets that would have previously required ground-blasted nuclear weapons to destroy.<br>
<br>
About the only reason to use nukes would be to get back at another NCB attack.  Whoever does a nuclear, chemical or biological attack on the US will either be suicidal or will try very hard not to be found out.  If they're found out they probably won't last long whether nukes are used or not and if they aren't then there's no point nuking anyone without proof.<br>
<br>
